content: <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  <reference anchor='I-D.aartsetuijn-nipst'> <front> <title>A method for network initiated partial session transfers</title>  <author initials='A' surname='Tuijn' fullname='Aartse Tuijn'>     <organization /> </author>  <author initials='D' surname='Bijwaard' fullname='Dennis Bijwaard'>     <organization /> </author>  <date month='February' day='28' year='2007' />  <abstract><t>This document describes a SIP-based method for network initiated partial session transfers that works together with terminal initiated partial session transfers. It uses the Mobile Node Control Mode for terminal initiated partial session transfers and it extends this method to support network initiated partial session transfers.</t></abstract>  </front>  <seriesInfo name='Internet-Draft' value='draft-aartsetuijn-nipst-00' /> <format type='TXT'         target='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-aartsetuijn-nipst-00.txt' /> </reference>
